  "notes": [
    "All transfer applicants must meet the University of California admissions eligibility requirements and the campus’s admission selection criteria. All requirements must be completed by the end of the spring term prior to transfer. For more information on UC admissions eligibility and admission to UC Santa Cruz, visit the Admissions website . The UC Santa Cruz Transfer Admission Guarantee (TAG) is a formal agreement that guarantees your fall admission to your chosen major, provided you are transferring from a California Community College and meet specific requirements. Visit the UC Santa Cruz TAG webpage for more information.",
    "THIS IS A SCREENING MAJOR. Screening majors require completion of specific preparatory coursework and/or a minimum GPA. For details on the specific screening requirements for this major, refer to the \" Transfer Admission Screening Policy \" below. Additional coursework listed under \"Recommended Preparation\" is not required for admission but is strongly recommended to support timely degree completion. For more information, including a list of screening majors and non-screening majors , visit the UCSC Admissions website.",
    "Some Advanced Placement (AP), International Baccalaureate Higher Level (IBH), and Advanced Level (A-level) exams satisfy UCSC course requirements. UCSC's exam credit policies may be found on the Degree Progress Unit website .",
    "Global Economics B.A. Transfer Admission Screening Policy Transfer students must complete the following three courses, or their articulated equivalents, with a grade of C (2.0) or better in each course, and a cumulative minimum GPA of 2.8 in all required screening courses , by the end of the spring term prior to transferring in the fall: ECON 1 – Introductory Microeconomics: Resource Allocation and Market Structure ECON 2 – Introductory Macroeconomics: Aggregate Economic Activity ONE of the following calculus courses: AM 11A – Mathematical Methods for Economists I MATH 11A – Calculus with Applications MATH 19A – Calculus for Science, Engineering, and Mathematics Refer to the \"Required Major Preparation Courses\" section below for lists of courses approved to fulfill these requirements. Strongly Recommended Major Preparation In addition to the required courses listed above, transfer students are strongly advised to complete the courses listed in the \"Recommended Preparation\" section below. These courses are prerequisites for upper-division courses required for the major. Students who do not complete these preparatory courses before transferring will likely need additional quarters of enrollment to complete their degree. Language Requirement The Global Economics B.A. requires a minimum of two years of study in a language relevant to the student’s chosen regional area of interest. Fluency in a language other than English is essential for students planning to engage in the global economy. Transfer students who meet the screening criteria outlined above and have completed two years of language study can complete the major within two years of transferring to UC Santa Cruz. For more details, refer to the Academic Planner section under the \"Requirements and Planners\" tab in the UC Santa Cruz General Catalog . Additional Information for Transfer Students are strongly encouraged to prioritize required and recommended major preparation courses and may additionally complete courses that fulfill UC Santa Cruz general education requirements before transferring as time allows. Please visit the Economics website to learn more about this major. UC Santa Cruz General Catalog: Global Economics B.A. Program Statement"
